opportunities.name: MODERN ADULT CONTEMPORARY ARTISTS
opportunities.request_description:
MODERN ADULT CONTEMPORARY ARTISTS or BANDS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by the Senior V.P. of A&R at a Major Record Label that's searching for Fresh, New Talent!

This A&R Executive is searching for acts that would appeal to fans of these references:

"Chemtrails Over The Country Club" by Lana Del Rey

"My Love Mine All Mine" by Mitski

"What Was I Made For?" by Billie Eilish

Please submit well-crafted Adult Contemporary Songs that could be heard on a playlist with the references! Memorable melodies, subdued rhythms, meaningful hooks, solid arrangements, and well-written lyrics are all needed for this opportunity. Modern Adult Contemporary instrumentation in the general wheelhouse of the references will work best. Please make sure any virtual sounds or samples you use are high quality, realistic, and not dated-sounding. Compelling, expressive, and well-performed vocals are the way to go!

IMPORTANT: This Executive is interested in artists and bands that have gained some traction from actively working on their careers. Please detail (in your bio) what you are doing with your career. Include any impressive touring, fan base, sales, streaming, or social media figures. That said – if you’re a new artist or band just starting out and don’t have much of a story or track record, but you DO have an amazing sound and some killer Songs to back it up, they still want to hear you!

TAXI Tip: We recommend submitting at least 2 Songs per submission so they can see if you’ve got depth in your material.

Your recording quality needs to be clean, clear, and well-balanced so that it represents your Songs well. Do NOT copy the referenced examples in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for texture and tone.

Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD, and please include lyrics, photos, and a bio. All submissions will be screened by a TAXI A&R Team Member who has a strong relationship with the Executive. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Tuesday, April 23rd, 2024. TAXI # S240423AC

opportunities.name: SOULFUL BLUES ROCK SONGS
opportunities.request_description:
SOULFUL BLUES ROCK SONGS with Male Vocals are needed for an (up to) $150, Direct-to-Film Producer placement in an upcoming Independent Feature Film that's currently in post-production!

Note: You'll get 100% of the sync fee, and keep 100% of your publishing and master rights. No publishing splits.

This Film's Producer is looking for Mid-Tempo Songs with Male Vocals that could work as a replacement for "Soulshine" by Allman Brothers, which is currently temped in:

"Soulshine" by Allman Brothers

They're NOT looking for clones or soundalikes! Similar tempo, style, and overall vibe? Yes. Clones? No!

IMPORTANT: Because the scene is already edited, matching (or being close to) the tempo of the reference is strongly recommended.

Please submit Blues Rock Songs with a hopeful vibe, soulful melodies, engaging grooves, and well-crafted lyrics. Instrumentation that's in the general wheelhouse of the reference Song will work best for this opportunity (think electric guitars, organ, drums, bass, etc.) Please ensure any virtual instruments or samples you use are high-quality and realistic. Well-performed, expressive, and soulful Male vocals are needed.

Lyrics should avoid references to specific names, places, dates, times, brands, and profanity. Please do NOT copy the referenced artist or song in any way, shape, or form. Use it as a general guide for tempo, tone, and overall vibe. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

The license fee for this placement is (up to) $150, depending on the ultimate use. This is a Direct-to-Producer placement, so you’ll keep 100% ownership of your Copyright and Master Recordings, plus you’ll also get 100% of the License Fee and any applicable performance royalties. You must own or control your Copyright and Master Recordings to pitch for this opportunity. Please submit as many Songs as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Thursday, April 25th, 2024. TAXI # S240425SH

opportunities.name: Lots of HAPPY, KID-FRIENDLY INSTRUMENTALS and/or
opportunities.request_description:
Lots of HAPPY, KID-FRIENDLY INSTRUMENTALS and/or INSTRUMENTAL CUES are needed by a Great Music Licensing Company with lots of Film and TV placements.

This Library is looking for several Instrumentals (and/or Cues) in the general stylistic ballpark of the following references:

High Fives - CBC Kids

Stuck in the Quinceanera - Stuck in the Middle (from 10:44 to12:05)

Sweet Tooth! - DC Super Hero Girls (from 0:13 - 1:10)

Please submit well-crafted Instrumentals and/or Instrumental Cues that create an overall happy, fun, bouncy, and positive vibe and feel for kids/preteen programming, promos, and entertainment. Your submissions should have uplifting motifs, feel-good grooves, lots of emotionally upbeat energy, and excellent arrangements. Instrumentation in the general ballpark of the references will suit your submissions best – think keys, claps, vibraphone, synths, bass, drums, funky guitar, etc. Please be sure any virtual instruments or sounds you use are high-quality and not dated-sounding.

Your submissions should be roughly 1.5 minutes long for Cues, and about 2 to 4 minutes long for Instrumentals, give or take. Non-faded, buttoned/stinger endings will work best. Please do NOT copy the referenced artists or songs in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a guide for tempo, texture, and tone. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This company offers an EXCLUSIVE deal, so please be sure the Instrumentals and/or Cues you pitch for this opportunity are NOT already signed with any other Companies or Catalogs. Any sync fees will be split 50/50 with the Company. You'll get 100% of the Writer's share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's share. You must own or control your Masters and Copyright to submit. Please submit as many Instrumentals and/or Cues as you'd like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Tuesday, April 23rd, 2024. TAXI # S240423HL

opportunities.request_description:
Lots of KLEZMER SONGS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by an extremely busy Music Library with a tremendously long list of killer placements in Hit TV Shows!

This A-List Company is on the lookout for Songs in the general stylistic ballpark of the following references:

"Zol shoyn kumen di geule" by The Klezmatics

"Basarabye" by Itzhak Perlman

"Yidl Mitn Fidl" by Zalmen Mlotek ft. Eleanor Reissa

Please submit well-crafted Klezmer Songs with infectious rhythms, stellar musicianship, and tons of Klezmer charm (think Fiddler on the Roof-style). Your submissions should have authentic melodies, danceable rhythms, solid arrangements, and well-crafted lyrics in Yiddish. Instrumentation should be in the general stylistic wheelhouse of traditional Klezmer music, with instruments such as Accordion, Acoustic Guitar, Nylon String Guitar, Bass Guitar, Hand Percussion, Tambourine, Strings, Concert Flute, Cimbalom (Dulcimer), Orchestral Harp, Trumpet, Piano, and Drumset. Performances should feel authentic – complete with traditional Klezmer articulations (bending the notes, forcing the breath, breathing into the notes, legato, staccato, etc.).

If you're using any virtual instruments, be sure they're super high-quality and realistic sounding. This request is all about capturing an authentic Klezmer vibe and sound!

TAXI Tip: Your submissions don't need to be in one rigid tempo throughout. Historically, Klezmer music was meant for dancing, so tempos were fluid – often players slightly led or trailed the beat creating a lilting sound. Because of this, it'd actually probably be a good idea to let the rhythms of your pieces flow freely in a rubato style so they feel more authentic. The more your pieces feel like they're being performed by a real Klezmer band, the better!

Lyrics need to be in Yiddish and should avoid references to specific names, dates, times, places, brands, and profanity. Non-faded, buttoned/stinger endings are strongly recommended. Do NOT copy the reference tracks in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, and overall vibe. Broadcast Quality is needed.

IMPORTANT: This Library really wants to find top-notch Composers – not just people who combine different samples or loops without altering them at all.  Cleared sample libraries are okay to use, but any samples or loops you include in your pieces should be altered enough that they're distinguishable from the originals. Basically, if you Shazamed one of your tracks and another artist's song comes up, your music would definitely be disqualified by this Company.

ALSO IMPORTANT: Your Submissions can NOT be commercially released on Spotify, Apple Music, etc., OR be encumbered by ANY other publishing, licensing, administration, and/or exploitation deals (whether non-exclusive or exclusive), including publishing/licensing agreements with CD Baby Pro, TuneCore, etc.

opportunities.request_description:

This Company is searching for a range of Instrumentals in the general stylistic ballpark of the following references:

"Heyser Bulgar" by Yxalag

"Freilach" by Klezmer Festival Band

"Klezmer Kaos" by Froggy Kaos

Please submit well-crafted Klezmer Instrumentals with infectious rhythms, stellar musicianship, and tons of Klezmer charm (think Fiddler on the Roof-style). Your submissions should have authentic melodies, excellent musicianship, danceable rhythms, and solid arrangements with plenty of forward motion and interest. Instrumentation should be in the general stylistic wheelhouse of traditional Klezmer music, with instruments such as Accordion, Acoustic Guitar, Nylon String Guitar, Bass Guitar, Hand Percussion, Tambourine, Strings, Concert Flute, Cimbalom (Dulcimer), Orchestral Harp, Trumpet, Piano, and Drumset.  Performances should feel authentic – complete with traditional Klezmer articulations (bending the notes, forcing the breath, breathing into the notes, legato, staccato, etc.).

If you're using any virtual instruments, be sure they're super high-quality and realistic sounding. This request is all about capturing an authentic Klezmer vibe and sound!

TAXI Tip: Your submissions don't need to be in one rigid tempo throughout. Historically, Klezmer music was meant for dancing, so tempos were fluid – often players slightly led or trailed the beat creating a lilting sound. Because of this, it'd actually probably be a good idea to let the rhythms of your pieces flow freely in a rubato style so they feel more authentic. The more your pieces feel like they're being performed by a real Klezmer band, the better!

All submissions should be about 2 to 4 minutes long, give or take. Non-faded, buttoned endings are strongly recommended. Do NOT copy the reference tracks in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, and overall vibe. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of ANY other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

IMPORTANT: This Library really wants to find top-notch Composers – not just people who combine different samples or loops without altering them at all. Cleared sample libraries are okay to use, but any samples or loops you include in your pieces should be altered enough that they're distinguishable from the originals. Basically, if you Shazamed one of your tracks and another artist's song comes up, your music would definitely be disqualified by this Company.

ALSO IMPORTANT: Your Submissions can NOT be commercially released on Spotify, Apple Music, etc., OR be encumbered by ANY other publishing, licensing, administration, and/or exploitation deals (whether non-exclusive or exclusive), including publishing/licensing agreements with CD Baby Pro, TuneCore, etc. Distribution agreements are fine. opportunities.name: Beats needed for TV & Online Advertising Campaigns in South Korea ($500-$14,000 per use)
opportunities.request_description:
All rights TV & Online Advertising Campaigns in South Korea ($500-$14,000 per use)Currently seeking “beats” for use in TV & Online advertising campaigns in South Korea! 
,br>  
When I say “beats”, I mean any tracks that are driven by a breakbeat, as one, if not the most dominant part of the track. Ie, Drum & Bass, Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Electronica, Edm, Trap, Grime, Experimental etc. 
  
All tracks must be upbeat and have a “Phat Beat”, “Killer Beat”, “Sick Beats”, “Dope Beat” or whatever your preferred description would be. 
   
Music must be well produced, high-quality, mixed and mastered. Instrumental tracks preferred please, but great vocal tracks can be accepted too (if you can supply instrumental versions even better) and all tempos considered. 
  
Artists must own all rights to their music 100% on both sides and there must be no copyright infringement. All music will be listened to, reviewed and feedback given.  
  
The average cost of TV advertising commercial in Korea is $800 to $1,500 per track, and for worldwide rights up to $14,000. 
   
The average cost of Online & YouTube advertising in Korea is $500-$2500 (geo restricted for single country of Korea), and worldwide use for $3000-$5000.  
  
Selected tracks be sent to clients in South Korea and music licensed on a non-exclusive basis (so you maintain all rights to your music), we simply go 50-50 on deals we get and you're paid quarterly.   
 
The South Korean market is built on a unique structure, which is not the same as any foreign market structure around the world. Because of this Korea has a higher advertising music fee than most other countries. This may be due to systemic limitations that the performing royalties cannot be collected, but also because there is no subsequent secondary payment after the initial payment of music fees. The total amount paid in Korea is 100% mechanical payout. 
  
Clients who will be using music in South Korea; Korea's major advertising agencies including the CHEIL and INOCEAN and brands such as; Samsung, LG, Hyundai and SK to name a few. 
  
If you make “beats’ I really look forward to hearing from you ! 
  
All the best,  
- Giles Gale -
Music supervisor, sync & Licensing Manager - Resonant Music Licensing

lyrics_ideas: "Climb Your Mountain" — The song focuses on an individual facing seemingly insurmountable challenges but continues to strive towards their peak. Each verse builds on the struggle, interwoven with imagery of rocky terrain and stormy weather, symbolizing the obstacles in life. The chorus rings out with a powerful, catchy melody, urging listeners to "climb your mountain, reach the sky," encapsulating the passion and determination required to chase dreams.

"Light of Dawn" — This track tells the story of a protagonist who starts off lost in the dark, metaphorically speaking, unable to find their path. As the song progresses, it details their journey of self-discovery and perseverance despite the hardships. The chorus celebrates the breakthrough moment with a thrilling, motivational beat and lyrics like, "Chase the light of dawn, through the fight, stand strong," emphasizing resilience and the joy of pursuing passions.

"Break the Chains" — Here, the lyrics delve into the theme of breaking free from the constraints that hold one back, whether they be fear, doubt, or societal expectations. Verses narrate personal stories of overcoming these barriers, while the chorus offers an anthem-like, catchy melody shouting "Break the chains, take the reins," inspiring listeners to take control of their destiny and never give up on their dreams.

lyrics_ideas: **"Climbing the Ladder"**

The song is an anthem for perseverance, following an individual through their journey of overcoming various life challenges to achieve their dreams. The lyrics detail the early mornings and late nights filled with hard work and dedication, facing setbacks yet continuing to push forward. The chorus is uplifting and motivational, repeating the mantra, "Keep climbing, never stop, every rung takes you up," symbolizing the continuous journey toward personal goals and aspirations.
**"Horizon Calling"**

This track tells the story of a protagonist who starts with humble beginnings but dreams big. Each verse explores different phases of their life where they encounter and overcome obstacles, drawing strength from their inner hope and unwavering determination. The chorus echoes the theme of relentless pursuit, with lines like, "Chase the horizon, it's calling your name, bound by no fears, ignite your flame." The lyrics aim to inspire listeners to remain hopeful and persistent, no matter the difficulties they face.
**"Dream Weaver"**

Reflecting a more introspective and poetic approach, this song delves into the emotional and spiritual aspects of pursuing one's passions. The lyrics invite listeners to weave their dreams into reality through creativity and vision. Phrases like, "In the fabric of the stars, stitch your dreams, weave them large," adorn the verses, while the chorus offers a catchy and empowering reminder: "Dream weaver, cast your net, catch the stars, on your path set." This song aims to resonate deeply with those who see their journey as not just a pursuit of goals, but as a form of personal expression and fulfillment.

lyrics_ideas: The lyrics is about a small-town singer who dreams of making it big in Nashville, overcoming challenges and setbacks along the way. As the song progresses, it builds up the excitement of finally getting noticed after playing in local bars and small venues. The climax of the song reaches as the singer gets a call from Universal Music Group Nashville, offering them a spot on their roster. The energy then drops as the artist reflects on the long nights and sacrifices made, appreciating the journey to stardom.

The song tells the story of a farmer's daughter who leaves her small rural life behind pursuing a music career, battling doubts and the fear of failure. The narrative builds as she gains confidence and strength, proving doubters wrong with each performance. Eventually, she lands a major break through her unique blend of traditional and modern country sounds, which reflects the kind of music Universal Music Group Nashville seeks. The bridge captures a poignant moment where she looks back at her humble beginnings, recognizing the immense effort and emotional toll it took to reach her dreams.

The lyrics describe a seasoned musician reflecting on their long career, from playing in dive bars to large arenas. The song details the highs of performing on stage and the lows of the music industry, building intensity with each verse as the musician's fame grows. The turning point comes when the musician contemplates retirement, realizing the true cost of their success — personal sacrifices and lost loves. The song concludes with a powerful, reflective chorus about being grateful for the journey and continuing to inspire upcoming artists.

Is your career ready for the next big step? 



If you're looking to get signed and become famous (or even just improve your game), then you owe it to yourself to stop what you're doing right now.



Steve Tramposch has been a Senior A&R exec for some of the world’s largest record and music companies, including Capitol, Virgin, Elektra, Eleven Seven, Billboard, and more.



He’s been doing this for over 20 years, and in that time, he’s been instrumental in the early discovery of artists that have sold tens of millions of records. Rock, Pop, Alternative, Rap, R&B, Singer-Songwriter, Country, Indie, you name it.


He was responsible for signing Nothing More, Red Jumpsuit Apparatus, The Format, and many, many more, and you can be next.


Forget blindly sending in music, waiting on long audition lines, or companies that promise they’ll send it to someone like Steve if they think you’re good enough.



Steve’s going to personally consult with you and give you the FAST TRACK ROUTE to achieving your dreams.



On any given day Steve is working with any number of artists and companies, fielding offers in a large number of different capacities – record, publishing, TV/film, tours, endorsements, you name it.



When you submit your music, send as much information as possible including links to social profiles, lyrics, social stats, touring stats, etc. 



Thanks for visiting, click "Submit to this Opportunity" and let's get started. 



Hope to hear from you, see you inside.

opportunities.name: Christmas music required All rights £100-£10,000 per use
opportunities.request_description:
Christmas music required All rights £100-£10,000 per use Hey guys!

I'm currently seeking Christmas songs, jingles, bed tracks etc that are suitable for advertising & marketing campaigns! 

Music must be original, well produced, mixed and mastered. Instrumental music preferred please, but great vocals welcome (but please make sure you can supply instrumental version as well) and all tempos, required.  

Additionally, covers of old classics such as Silent Night which are copyright free would be great too!

Artists must own all rights to their music 100% and there must be no copyright infringement.  

Selected tracks will be pro-actively pitched to our clients for relevant sync opportunities for use in their Christmas campaigns. Clients are film & video production companies, advertising agencies and a few game developers that make high-end content. 

Music used by clients will be licensed on a non-exclusive basis (so you maintain all rights to your music), simply go 50-50 on deals we get for you, you’re paid quarterly and keep 100% of all royalties generated from placements. Artist's will receive between £100-£10,000 per use depending on use, type of project etc, so, if you have any great Christmas music for sync, I’d really love to hear from you! 

NB; If you have already submitted and had music accepted into our catalogue that is suitable for this brief, you don’t need to re-submit as your music will automatically be pitched to our clients. Thanks! 

Looking forward to hearing and working with you :) 
 
All the best, 
Giles Gale 
Music Supervisor

A story of a small-town person moving to a big city during the holiday season to chase their dreams of becoming an artist. The lyrics capture the mix of nostalgia for home and the excitement of new opportunities, using the festive background as a metaphor for the lights and promises of the city. The song builds up from uncertainty to a powerful reaffirmation of self-belief and determination.

A narrative of a group of friends who come together to put on a Christmas play, facing and overcoming various obstacles along the way. The song highlights each challenge with a light-hearted and motivational tone, emphasizing teamwork and the spirit of the season. The chorus celebrates the fulfillment and happiness found in creative expression and community during the joyous time of Christmas.

Deal Type: Catalog Inclusion
Decision Maker: I'm the final decision maker
Deal Structure: Exclusive
Compensation: $25,000 - $50,000
Song Quality: Fully mastered, Broadcast ready
Similar Sounding Artists: Black Keys, Jack White, Hanni El Khatib, Whitestripes 

Why the higher than average submission fee?
Often we hear music that doesn’t make the final cut for a particular opportunity but we go ahead and select the song anyway because we believe the song is appropriate for other opportunities we’re working on. Here at Music of The Sea, we fill dozens of sync requests every week. We don’t have time to listen to everything so the higher submission fee tends to discourage all but the best - and we sign a lot of music and we place almost all of it. 

We only offer one deal and the terms are the same for everyone, so don’t submit if you’re seeking another type of deal. If we select your song, you give us exclusive rights to the song for 5 years. If after 5 years we haven’t licensed your song, the rights revert back to you. If we do license your song, we share in the revenue. Often, if we love the song we hear and want to work with you we will also have interest in hearing other songs in your catalog and possibly doing a broader deal.

The words evoke images of speeding through city streets, defying norms and escaping the mundane, embodying the thrill and allure of living in the moment.

The lyrics celebrate the story of an outsider who challenges the status quo with a fierce independence. It captures their journey, characterized by bold, confrontational stances against societal expectations, and culminates in a powerful realization of the individual's impact on the world. The soundtrack complements this narrative with raw, intense rock elements that emphasize the theme of defiance.

The lyrics describe a personal revolution where the protagonist decides to break free from societal chains and expectations, exploring themes of self-discovery and autonomy. Set against a backdrop of hard-hitting rock music, the song resonates with anyone who has ever felt suppressed by their circumstances and yearns for freedom. Each verse builds on this idea, climaxing in a chorus that is both anthemic and empowering.

opportunities.name: Looking for that Somethin' Special
opportunities.request_description:
Looking for that Somethin' SpecialSometimes you hear a song and it hit you right between the ears, it sticks in your head and jumps up at you last thing at night, cleaning the yard, driving your car and you go "Damn that's catchy".

Well with thirty years in the business (Top Ten Writer /  Producer and performer, including writing for the wonderful Gloria Gaynor) I have spotted songs well before they were polished into a hit. My friend played me a rough demo and wasn't sure about it. I nearly fainted, "That's Top Ten my friend" I told him.

I was wrong. It went to Number One in the UK for three weeks!

I hear hits. It's in my DNA. So let me hear what you have and I will give you my brutally honest critique. I will not blow smoke at you. I will tell you what I think and what could be done (if needed) to make it better. 

Obviously if I love it then I will want to talk business with you too but that is for later.

OK the future is yours for the taking.

Musically yours, Tim H

Is your career ready for the next big step? 



If you're looking to get signed and become famous (or even just improve your game), then you owe it to yourself to stop what you're doing right now.



Steve Tramposch has been a Senior A&R exec for some of the world’s largest record and music companies, including Capitol, Virgin, Elektra, Eleven Seven, Billboard, and more.



He’s been doing this for over 20 years, and in that time, he’s been instrumental in the early discovery of artists that have sold tens of millions of records. Rock, Pop, Alternative, Rap, R&B, Singer-Songwriter, Country, Indie, you name it.


He was responsible for signing Nothing More, Red Jumpsuit Apparatus, The Format, and many, many more.


Forget blindly sending in music, waiting on long audition lines, or companies that promise they’ll send it to someone like Steve if they think you’re good enough.



Steve’s going to personally review and send you a professional critique of your song.



On any given day Steve is working with any number of artists fielding offers in a large number of different capacities – record, publishing, TV/film, tours, endorsements, you name it.


When you submit your music, send as much information as possible including links to social profiles, lyrics, social stats, touring stats, etc. 



A few notes: Audio quality is not a deciding factor, talent is. For music, singing a cover is ok if you cannot record and submit an original.


Thanks for visiting, click "Submit to this Opportunity" and let's get started. 


Hope to hear from you, see you inside.

The chorus reverberates with optimism and success, celebrating the strength found in enduring love and shared battles.

There are more cues to come and I will update this as they come.

Grand Northern Group
lyrics_ideas: The lyrics recount the journey of an old cowboy reflecting on his lost love, interweaving themes of heartache and healing. As he rides through the open fields of Mississippi, he reminisces about the highs and lows of their time together, ultimately finding peace in the memories and the lessons learned from loving and losing.

The song tells the story of a woman returning to her family's Mississippi farm after years away, exploring her mixed feelings of nostalgia and the pain of what she left behind. It delves into her connections with her past loves and the personal growth that comes from embracing her roots and the bittersweet reunions.

The narrative focuses on a small-town musician grappling with the death of his lifelong partner. Using a blend of folk and bluegrass, the lyrics explore his profound sense of loss but gradually shift to a more hopeful tone as he finds solace in music and the community around him, illustrating his journey from despair to acceptance and rediscovery of joy.

opportunities.name: Artists only please: Detailed Evaluation & Review
opportunities.request_description:
Artists only please: Detailed Evaluation & ReviewArtists Only: Detailed Evaluation & Review
If your passion is to entertain and edify people with your talent, this is your opportunity to be heard. We are looking for artists with exceptional, recognizable voices and styles to sign to our artist development company. Your ability to write your own songs is a plus but not a necessity.
Please give us a detailed description of your performing experience, artists with whom you identify and who have influenced you, known artist(s) for whom you could open, and the amount of touring you would be able to do based on your relationships and/or job. If you would like us to hear complete songs, submit them, or if you'd rather give us a taste of some different songs, you can submit a show reel medley not longer than five minutes. For every submission, we'll open a conversation with you so we can go further than just a critique of the submission. That conversation will stay open until we've given you every observation and piece of advice we can think of. We won't mince words, so be prepared to get an extremely detailed and honest evaluation of your talent, including what we think your strengths and weaknesses are and what we believe your chances of making it as an artist would be. A small percentage of artists rise to the top. If you aspire to be in that number, let us hear from you. This opportunity is somewhat higher in price than the average opportunity on Xray because we will take the time to deeply evaluate your songs, videos and links. We can't guarantee that we will be able to work with you, but at the minimum, you'll benefit from our 50 years experience in the music industry.- Warren Ells -
Owner - SeaSoDeep Music and SeaBeyondShore Music ASCAP

Climb the mountains, no time to rest.
Battling storms, fighting the tide,
With dreams in our hearts, we ride.

Through the highs and the lows.
Every challenge, you'll overcome,
Until the day your dreams are won."

"Verse: Broken wings but a soul on fire,
Kindling passions, rising higher.
A path of stars laid out for thee,
In pursuit of what you're meant to be.
Chorus: Fly toward your dreams, reach the sky,
Lift your spirit, aim so high.
Each hurdle crossed, an anthem sung,
In the race of life, forever young."

"Verse: Run through shadows, chase the light,
Every dawn ends the darkest night.
Failure’s moment but teaches best,
March on forward, ignore the rest.
Chorus: Journey far to chase your dreams,
With rivers wide and endless streams.
Though the path seems long and winding,
Every step brings you closer to finding."

If you have music in our catalog, your music is automatically being considered. 

- Eddie Sea / Music Of The Sea 

Why the higher than average submission fee?
Often we hear music that doesn’t make the final cut for a particular opportunity but we go ahead and select the song anyway because we believe the song is appropriate for other opportunities we’re working on. Here at Music of The Sea, we fill dozens of sync requests every week. We don’t have time to listen to everything so the higher submission fee tends to discourage all but the best - and we sign a lot of music and we place almost all of it. 

We only offer one deal and the terms are the same for everyone, so don’t submit if you’re seeking another type of deal. If we select your song, you give us exclusive rights to the song for 3 years. If after three years we haven’t licensed your song, the rights revert back to you. If we do license your song, we share in the revenue. Often, if we love the song we hear and want to work with you we will also have interest in hearing other songs in your catalog and possibly doing a broader deal.

opportunities.name: Song Critiques & Career Coaching From Reggie Calloway
opportunities.request_description:
Song Critiques & Career Coaching From Reggie CallowayReggie Calloway is eager to offer you his ear, taste, and professional criteria to make your music better, more adapted to what the industry is currently seeking, and general songwriting advice.

Additionally, and based on the questions you ask in the submission message space, Reggie will answer specific questions about your career path and strategy.

The five time Grammy-nominated Reggie Calloway has always displayed a unique ear for music and trends. It is no surprise that the music pioneer received a Grammy nomination for R&B Songwriter of the Year for the hit song “Casanova” in 1987.

Best known as the founder and leader of one of the most popular Techno-funk bands, Midnight Star, Calloway led the group to international success by writing, producing and arranging a string of top mega #1 hits including, “Operator,” “No Parking On The Dance Floor,” “I Wanna Be Rich” and “Freak-a-zoid.”

One of Calloway’s original compositions entitled, “I’ll Be Good For You,” was featured on N’Sync’s multi-platinum CD, No Strings Attached (highest selling album of the last decade). He has also penned songs for the chart-topping group Levert (“Casanova”), the sultry Teddy Pendergrass (“Joy”), Grammy-winning Gladys Knight (“Love Overboard”) and “Jump Start My Love” for Natalie Cole.

opportunities.request_description:
In need of written materialRecord label looking for songwriters for one of our female vocalists. L7 Music Group is a worldwide digital distribution, publishing and licensing company that strives to take indie artists, from all genres, to the next level. We were founded in February 2017 with over 40 years of hands-on experience in the music industry, collectively. Our growing company excels in getting artists’ music to the masses and getting them paid for their musical works. Unlike most distribution services, we do not charge a fee to distribute with our company. Instead, we split the profits with our artists 80-20, with the artist taking the lion’s share of the profits from their music. We distribute to over 250 downloading & streaming markets and have an 85% success rate on getting artists music in rotation on Pandora. We realize that times have changed and that the method of hand-to-hand CD sells is slowing diminishing, so we've decided to assist artists in building an online presence by offering our services to those artists who really want to be heard, foreign and domestic.- Geoffrey Domingues -
CEO - L7 Music Group

The bridge could highlight a moment of self-reflection and the realization of the personal sacrifices made for her art.

Why the higher than average submission fee?

Often we hear music that doesn’t make the final cut for a particular opportunity but we go ahead and select the song anyway because we believe the song is appropriate for other opportunities we’re working on. Here at Music of The Sea, we fill dozens of sync requests every week. We don’t have time to listen to everything so the higher submission fee tends to discourage all but the best - and we sign a lot of music and we place almost all of it.

opportunities.name: Emotive Cinematic Electronic & Orchestral Music Needed (£50-£1000 per use)
opportunities.request_description:
Emotive Cinematic Electronic & Orchestral Music Needed (£50-£1000 per use) Seeking emotive and uplifting Cinematic music for use in documentaries, film and TV/Streaming. 

Music must be original, well produced, mixed and mastered. Instrumental music preferred please, but great vocals welcome (please make sure you can supply instrumental version as well) and all tempos / emotions and genres required from electronica to big orchestral. 

Artists must control all rights to their music 100% on both sides (master & publishing) and there must be no copyright infringement.  

Selected tracks will be cleared into our catalogue, pro-actively pitched to sync opportunities and made available for existing clients to use in their projects. Clients are professional film makers, video production companies, indie film makers, games developers and advertising agencies that make high-end film content. 

Music used by clients will be licensed on a non-exclusive basis (so you maintain all rights to your music), we simply go 50-50 on deals we get for you, you’re paid quarterly and artists keep 100% of all royalties generated from placements. 
 
Artist's will receive between £50-£1,000 per track depending on use, size of project etc, and music will be made available for other suitable licensing opportunities. So, if you have any amazing cinematic music, I’d really love to hear from you! 

NB; If you have already submitted and had music accepted into our catalogue that is suitable for this brief, you don’t need to re-submit as your music will automatically be pitched to our clients! 

Looking forward to hearing your music and working with you :) 
 
All the best, 
Giles Gale 

Music Supervisor

lyrics_ideas: **Overcoming Personal Hardships**: The lyrics tell the story of an individual struggling with personal challenges, possibly battling a tough phase in their life such as financial hardship, loss, or self-doubt. The music starts with a slow, melancholic melody that captures the weight of these challenges. As the song progresses, the melody transforms into an uplifting, triumphant tune reflecting the character's journey towards overcoming these adversities and finding hope and success, resonating with a broad audience in a relatable and motivational manner.

**Journey of Self-Discovery and Triumph**: This song follows the emotional journey of someone discovering their true self and potential against all odds. The lyrics depict scenes of introspection and realization, beginning with doubt and confusion represented by a slower, somber tone. As the character gains confidence and starts embracing their true self, the music shifts to a more dynamic, energetic, and joyful crescendo, symbolizing their triumphant emergence as a stronger, self-assured individual.

**Entrepreneurial Success Story**: The lyrics focus on an aspiring entrepreneur facing numerous setbacks and naysayers. Initially portrayed through a slower, reflective melody, the character's initial struggles with starting a business and encountering failures are laid bare. As they learn from their mistakes and persist in their endeavors, the music transitions into an uplifting and empowering sequence that celebrates their eventual success and the fulfillment of their dreams, aligning well with the idea of struggle turning into triumph.

lyrics_ideas: The lyrics of the song "Come On" tell the story of a young man's relentless pursuit of his musical dreams, despite facing numerous setbacks. With an energetic and motivational tone, the song encourages listeners to never give up, emphasizing that every step, every failure, is a part of the journey to success. The chorus is catchy and uplifting, directly addressing the listener with lines like "Come on, keep the fire alive, you're close to reaching skies!"

The song uses the metaphor of a journey to describe the process of chasing dreams. Each verse introduces different stages of the pursuit, from the initial spark of passion to the struggles and eventual breakthroughs. The lyrics provide inspiration by detailing the sheer determination needed to overcome obstacles, with lines such as "Climb every mountain, ford every stream, chase your dreams, let your spirit soar high."

"Come On" is crafted as an anthem for unity and camaraderie among the group members and their fans. The lyrics emphasize the power of collaboration and mutual support in achieving shared dreams. With a heartwarming bridge that underscores the importance of believing in each other, the song includes lines like "Together we stand, in the spotlight’s glare, hands in the air, voices strong and true!" This promotes a message of equality and partnership which aligns with the group’s ethos of each member having an equal voice.

lyrics_ideas: **Chasing Dreams on Dirt Roads:** The song revolves around a young person in a small town, blending elements of country life with aspirations fueled by hip-hop beats. The story details the struggles of chasing dreams where the big city lights meet country stars. Verses highlight the hard work and hurdles faced, building up to a powerful chorus about breaking barriers and achieving dreams against all odds. The bridge features a reflective moment, acknowledging the sacrifices made and the roots that keep them grounded.

**Crossroads Anthem:** This track captures the journey of an artist at the crossroads of genres, uniting the storytelling traditions of country with the rhythm and audacity of hip-hop. The lyrics narrate overcoming genre prejudice and musical battles, building to an exhilarating chorus celebrating the fusion of musical worlds. A quieter bridge reflects on the artist's identity crisis and the cultural blend that defines them, emphasizing the personal growth that comes with artistic innovation.

**Heart Beats in the Hometown:** Focused on the contrast between small-town values and big-city dreams, this song tells the story of a local hero who makes it big in the music industry but struggles with their new identity. The verses build intensity and pace, encapsulating the thrill of success and the energy of hip-hop, while the chorus brings a catchy, uplifting melody typical of pop country. The song drops into a reflective, slower-paced bridge where the singer reminisces about home, acknowledging the cost of their success.

opportunities.name: Offering song critiques for J-pop and K-pop markets
opportunities.request_description:
Offering song critiques for J-pop and K-pop marketsIn this dropbox, Audity Music is offering the opportunity for expert critique of your song with an eye towards helping you understand what is required to make records that work in the Japan and Korea markets. 

Audity has an especially strong niche in Asia, having relationships with top songwriters, producers, record labels, publishers and other key players that are difficult to rival. Our on-the-ground experience in Japan and Korea has given us the opportunity to develop a unique expertise in both markets. Now, we are offering to share our knowledge with you in order to boost your chances of successful pitching and placement in Asia. A lot of writers come to us seeking information about and access to the Asia markets. Here's your chance.

Why YOU should consider Asia?

Japan is the second largest music market in the world, not very far behind the U.S. in terms of annual music revenues. If you ignore Japan, you could be giving up substantial income as a songwriter; indeed you may find that income in Japan exceeds income in your home market if you can create the music sought in the Japanese market and have the right avenues in which to pitch it. Additionally, Korea is a very strong market in Asia that tends to lean a bit more Western in its music soundscape. the K-pop market has been growing increasingly strong in recent years, especially on the international scene as Korean record labels have been excellent as pushing K-Pop outside of Korea and even outside of Asia to Europe, America, South America, etc.

China/Taiwan is another growing force to be reckoned with and strongly considered by songwriters as China's intellectual property protection and licensing regime comes into form. You will find that all the major U.S. labels, Korean labels, Japanese labels, etc are now partnering with Chinese companies to be prepared for when China's regime truly comes online. And, Mandopop is a strong force in China, largely emanating from Taiwan.

If you want Audity Music's expertise on Asia markets for your benefit, submit here! We encourage writers to pursue the diversification of markets for their music and always have an international mindset. Music is the universal language after all!

If we REALLY like your song(s) and think has placement potential with some additional production/editing/co-writing, we may be in touch via direct message to work further with you and offer such services. And, if we think your song(s) is already a good fit for the markets, we may reach out to discuss representation of your music in Asia and beyond. Again, Asia is our particularly unique niche. However, we pitch music around the world. We're not here to just take fees. We want to find great writers and work with them! Our expert critiques will take time significantly more time than simply voting "Selected" or "Not Selected", thus the higher submission fee. 

Looking forward to hearing your songs!
- Audity Music, LLC

Often we hear music that doesn’t make the final cut for a particular opportunity but we go ahead and select the song anyway because we believe the song is appropriate for other opportunities we’re working on. Here at Music of The Sea, we fill dozens of sync requests every week. We don’t have time to listen to everything so the higher submission fee tends to discourage all but the best - and we sign a lot of music and we place almost all of it.

We don’t have time to listen to everything so the higher submission fee tends to discourage all but the best - and we sign a lot of music and we place almost all of it.

We only offer one deal and the terms are the same for everyone, so don’t submit if you’re seeking another type of deal. If we select your song, you give us exclusive rights to the song for 3 years. If after three years we haven’t licensed your song, the rights revert back to you. If we do license your song, we share in the revenue. Often, if we love the song we hear and want to work with you we will also have interest in hearing other songs in your catalog and possibly doing a broader deal.

opportunities.name: Hip Hop Tracks Needed (up to £1000+ per use)
opportunities.request_description:
"Family friendly" Hip Hop Tracks Needed (£50-£1000+ per use) 
Seeking new "Family Friendly" Hip Hop tracks suitable for use in TV/Streaming, advertising, online videos, documentaries and films. 

“Family friendly” means tracks that lyrics are "appropriate" for all the family, from your grandmother to your kids, with universal themes and no swearing, talking about drugs or graphic sexualised content etc. (Boring I know, but there is a massive gap in the market for family friendly hip hop that can be used on Netflix, HBO, Hulu shows etc!). 

Music must be original, well produced, mixed and mastered. "Family friendly" lyrics needed, but great instrumentals tracks always welcome (and please make sure you can supply instrumental versions of vocal tracks), and all emotions/styles required from experimental beats to party bangers. 

Artists must own/control all rights to their music 100% on both sides (master & publishing) and there must be no copyright infringement.  

Selected tracks will be cleared into our catalogue and made available for existing clients to use in their projects, and pro-actively pitched to sync opportunities. Clients are professional film makers, TV/video production companies, games developers, advertising agencies etc, that produce high-end content. 

Music used by clients will be licensed on a non-exclusive basis (so you maintain all rights to your music), we simply go 50-50 on deals we get for you, you’re paid quarterly and keep 100% of all royalties generated from placements. 
 
Artist's will receive between £50-£1,000+ per track depending on use, type of project etc, and music will be available for all licensing opportunities. So, if you have any amazing Hip Hop tracks, I’d really love to hear from you! 

NB; If you have already had music accepted into our catalogue that is suitable for this brief, you don’t need to re-submit as your music will automatically be pitched to our clients.

Looking forward to hearing your music and working with you!
 
All the best, 
Giles Gale 

Music Supervisor

opportunities.request_description:
Music Needed for YouTube Content CreatorsSeeking music for YouTube content creators!

I have started a new subscription service for YouTube content creators and seeking suitable music.

Music must be good vibes, positive and upbeat. All genres considered ie, Dance, Rock, Jazz, Electronica, Pop, R&B, Hip Hop, Classical, Orchestral, Ambient... etc. 

Music must be high-quality, mixed and mastered. Instrumental tracks preferred, but great vocal tracks accepted and please make sure you supply instrumental mix as well! 

All music will be listened to, reviewed and feedback given. Artists/rights holders must own all rights to their music (on both sides) and there must be no copyright infringement.

Selected tracks will be licensed on a non-exclusive basis (so you maintain all rights to your music), we simply go 50-50 split on income we generate for you, you'll be paid quarterly and you keep 100% of all backend royalties.

As well as YouTube videos, your music will also be made available to our B2B clients for traditional sync licensing deals. Clients are professional video/film production companies & advertising agencies that make high-quality content. Including brands; Oracle, Microsoft, JD Sports, The North Face, Asics, Addidas, Pringles, to name a few! 

For traditional sync deals artists will receive anywhere between £50-£10,000 per track depending on use, and there’s no limit the number of times a track can be licensed. So, if you have any great music we’d really love to hear from you! 

Any questions please feel free to ask and look forward to working with you :)

All the best, 
Giles

In today's music business there are a lot of bands and artists who deserve deals, but with the industry in the state it is and the uncertainty of labels giving new bands money, they now want to see some kind of exposure first and getting a song in a film or TV show is a massive step and one of the best chances of nailing the record deal, so with that in mind...

Alexander Johnston, head of the Grand Northern Group / Grand Northern Sync is an industry composer/producer and music supervisor for various Hollywood and Global Film Production companies, film producers and writers and he is regularly sought out by various companies to either compose or over see the music for the various projects.

He is looking for songs of all genres and styles for placement in film and TV, it really can be anything, he wants to hear it all, as he is a great believer in everything should have a chance and he is convinced there are real quality people out there not getting the shots they deserve

opportunities.name: REMOTE: Erzetich - Compilation CD
opportunities.request_comments:
The selection process:
1. we listen to your music – we prefer original genres that aren't easy to categorize,
2. if we like what we hear, we will ask you for a lossless audio file to check the quality of the recording,
3. if everything's fine, you're in.

Before you submit, be sure that:
1. you have an excellent recording in lossless format (FLAC or WAV),
2. you have a professionally taken photo in high resolution,
3. you have a professionally written bio.

What you get:
- 5 copies of the CD,
- distribution of the CD to the audiophile community (our partners, our customers, Hi-Fi show visitors, journalists, and established musicians/managers/producers that we're already working with),
- 50 % discount on any of our equipment.
opportunities.request_description:
We are accepting submissions for our 2nd compilation that will be printed onto an audiophile-grade gold-plated CD.

We are looking for music that is suitable for demonstrating high-end equipment, therefore music that is not only original and well-executed but the one that is also recorded and produced with above-average quality. Although we like energetic rock and metal, these and similar genres are the ones that we will have to skip for this project. All the rest is more than welcome.

As it was for our first compilation, this one will be either a giveaway to our partners and customers, as well as sold on our website for NO-PROFIT (only the cost of a physical CD, packaging, and shipping will be charged).

With this compilation, we aim to promote quality artists (including their producers and audio engineers) along with our brand.
opportunities.request_opportunity_description: We put the music first by creating products for people, not for measuring instruments. It is important that our products sound right, pleasant, and musical. Technology is just a means to achieve that. Erzetich makes products that notable artists such as Imogen Heap, David Bottrill, Bill Gould, and many more love and rely on when producing. Our workshop is located in the Slovenian woods and thatâ€™s why we use a lot of (tilia) wood in our products. Despite our industrial/brutalist design approach, the (artificially aged) wood makes our products more organic and personal. By using sturdy materials we make our products long-lived and easily repairable, therefore sustainable. Being ourselves with the music background, we constantly work with established as well as independent musicians to promote their work and good sound.

opportunities.request_description:
Our Indie Promo Circuit is a marketing & opportunity platform designed specifically for Indie Talent in mind. Allowing each individual participate to have their talents seen, heard & curated with the opportunity to perform Live via IPC-Cam Connect or Live on stage at various studio venues. Participants will be selected from their submissions & will have the chance to“GET EXPOSURE”-“GET BOOKED”- “GET PAID” from global industry opportunities. The IPC is brought to you by Indie Movement - Club 47 Recording / ASCAP Publishing, and is open to ALL GENRES OF MUSIC and ENTERTAINMENT TALENTS. 

All participates are allowed to submit two (2) audition tracks and or videos. The participates selected will either be booked for upcoming performance gigs with some gigs offering compensation ranging from $50 - $1,000 or Free Major Promotional Exposure. Other offers include; Record Deals, Distribution Deals, Magazine Article Write-Up, Radio/TV Airplay & or Studio/Rehearsal Time. As well as Audio/Video Placement, Licensing, Publishing & Compilation Album/DVD Deals. Information will be posted on our website, explaining the benefits offered for each opportunity. 

For the participates that were not selected; could be chosen by our Industry Rep & receive Talent Development. We assist the talent by providing development training, studio / rehearsal time & other valuable resources to help prepare the talent for upcoming opportunities.

Our events & auditions will be filmed & streamed to over 100K viewers, as well as in front of crowds up to 5,000+ in attendance. Selected participates will be featured on our Compilation Album & DVD series. This includes worldwide major distribution for the series to over 200+ digital retail providers through The Orchard and ASCAP Publishing through Indie Movement / Club 47 Recording, reaching an audience of over 100 Million+. 

We also assist the talent with a Bio (Digital EPK) and a Promotional “Talent” Website Landing Page (When Applicable). We/re offering an incredible opportunity for a variety of talented participates. From indie artist, musicians, bands, cover bands, comedians, magicians, dance groups, dj’s, improv comedy acts, solo artist, music producers & the like from ALL OVER THE WORLD. 

If your looking to make a name for yourself in the music & entertainment industry, the time is now. We’ve collaborated with major & independent music & entertainment industry professionals to offer valuable and extremely tangible assistance, advice, industry deals and solid performance opportunities. Your submission will be seen, heard, curated, as well as provided honest feedback & make adjustments to your submissions (When applicable).

Our Events will be filmed, streamed and submitted to Major Networks to be televised & for syndication possibilities. Our event will be Promoted Through Major Network Radio & TV Ads, Internet TV & Radio, Websites, Social Media, Magazine Exposure & more, totaling over 80 Million+. Reaching a combined total audience of over 180 Million+.

opportunities.description:
Immersive Experiences & Conscious Collaborations
The Quintessence Coalition brings enthusiasm for crafting dynamic, visually striking and stimulating atmospheres, events, and experiences that encourages participation, nourishes culture, and cultivates good vibrations and wellbeing. Supporting Canadian virtuosities and performances through a multiplicity of creative and concerted endeavors.
Including performances from Allison Crowe (Zack Snyder’s Justice League, Army of the Dead), Brad Weber (Caribou, Pick a Piper, Coy Haste, BisonBison), ZUU (supporting and touring with artists such as Kelis, Rhye, Django Django, and Pumarosa), Johnny Voltik (who graced Glastonbury’s Shangri-La stage and who has supported and toured with such acts as Busta Rhymes, NERD, and Damien Marley), Sean Boots (of the Amateur Lovers who were signed with Loosegroove Records; Stone Gossard of Pearl Jam), Lindsey Alley (All New Mickey Mouse Club; starring alongside JC Chasez of NSYNC, and Keri Russell), and mystic, artist and writer White Owl Mystic (Elfie Kalfakis, whose adult-picture book entitled, Butterfly: A Tale of Misogyny and Systemic Abuse and White Owl Mystic Arcana, has been sold all around the world). Airing on Rogers TV (The Tom Green Show).

opportunities.request_description:
MODERN COUNTRY HITS with Male Vocals are needed by a phenomenal Publisher for a high-profile Country Star looking for new material!

This Publisher is on the hunt for slam-dunk Hits in All Tempos that could be heard on a playlist with the following references:

"What He'll Never Have (In The Woods)" by Dylan Scott 

"What My World Spins Around" by Jordan Davis

"Stars Like Confetti" by Dustin Lynch 

Please submit modern Country Songs with lots of mainstream appeal, down-home charm, and the potential to be the next chart-topping Country hit! Your submissions should have unforgettable choruses, ear-worm melodies, powerful rhythms, solid arrangements, and well-written lyrics. Modern Country instrumentation that's in the general stylistic wheelhouse of the references will work best for this pitch. Please make sure that any virtual instruments or samples you use are high quality and not dated-sounding. Expressive and well-performed Male vocals are key!

TAXI Tip: Vocal deliveries can often make or break Song pitches. Making sure that the vocals in your Songs are well-performed, compelling, and rich with Country authenticity will likely increase your chances of getting this Artist excited about your Songs!

Stripped-down demos and full productions are both okay to submit, as long as your Songs are great and your recordings are clean, clear, and well-balanced! Do NOT copy the references in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, texture, and overall vibe.

NOTEWORTHY: If time permits, someone from the Publisher's staff (who has been trained as a TAXI screener) will screen for this request. That means that somebody who is directly involved in this request could be "ears-on" with your submissions.

The specific deal points will be negotiated on a Song-by-Song basis directly with the Publisher. Please submit as many Songs as you like, online or per CD, and PLEASE include lyrics! Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Saturday, May 11th, 2024. TAXI # S240511CY

opportunities.request_description:
Sync Opp: Campaign for the Secret Boutique WhiskeyBrief Description: Sync Opp: Campaign for the Secret Boutique Whiskey.
 
We have a client looking for a track for a prestigious European Boutique Whiskey brand. (Identity undisclosed)

Creative Details from Client

 

Project Overview:

Develop a captivating campaign for the secret Boutique Whiskey, set to launch this year. The campaign emphasizes fearless creativity, aiming to resonate with audiences through compelling storytelling.

Music Requirement:

The selected track should exude an indie rock vibe akin to "Welcome to my Island," featuring a strong beat and uplifting vocals. The overall tone should channel the spirit of artists like Karen O and Caroline, with a distinct "left of the dial" appeal. The lyrics must strike a balance between relevance and neutrality, avoiding overly celebratory or melancholic themes. The emphasis lies on impactful vocals and a dynamic progression that complements the video narrative.

Client Preferences:

Preferably vocals-driven, with lyrics that resonate without veering into clichéd or overly empowering territory. The song should possess a certain edge while maintaining a universal appeal.


Exclusivity and Usage:

Exclusivity is granted to similar brands within the whiskey industry. The global campaign spans across various mediums, including social media, CTV/digital platforms (limited to the US and UK), and Out-of-Home advertising. Usage rights extend for one year across all channels, with paid media usage restricted to six months in the US, UK, and Sweden.

Budget:

Total budget allocation stands at $30,000 All-In (Less all Fees), covering all aspects of music acquisition and licensing.

Additional Notes:

Creativity and relevance are paramount in song selection, aligning closely with the brand's ethos and the campaign's overarching theme of fearless innovation.

Please include lyrics, Composer (PRO/IPI)

Broadcast Quality is needed.

You must own or control your Master and Copyright to pitch for this opportunity. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by our MMG team for quality purposes, then moved forward. If they decide to move forward we will contact you immediately. If you don't hear back within a week of the deadline then you can consider it a pass.

The verses would explore themes of introspection and the struggles encountered during this journey, culminating in a powerful revelation in the chorus that aligns with the brand's vision of breaking new ground and creating an unparalleled whiskey experience.

opportunities.request_opportunity_description: Celtic Roots Radio is a podcast dedicated to promoting traditional and contemporary Celtic music from around the world. Hosted by Raymond McCullough and Gerry McCullough, the podcast features interviews from a variety of guests including musicians, poets, writers, and historians to explore the rich cultural heritage of Celtic music.Since its launch in 2007, Celtic Roots Radio has developed a loyal following among music lovers and cultural enthusiasts. The show is available to stream or download on various platforms including iTunes, Spotify, and Soundcloud.Through its engaging interviews, informative segments, and captivating music, Celtic Roots Radio continues to inspire and educate audiences around the world about the timeless beauty and power of Celtic music.
opportunities.request_band_description: We are looking for artists and bands in the following categories:Celtic, folk, folk/rock, Irish, Scottish, Cajun, Breton/Breizh, Galician, Cape Breton, Appalachian, Mountain, acoustic, singer/songwriter and (sometimes) blues.We do NOT play any Country, heavy rock/metal or Reggae music!

opportunities.name: MAINSTREAM ADULT CONTEMPORARY/POP ARTISTS
opportunities.request_description:
MAINSTREAM ADULT CONTEMPORARY/POP ARTISTS or BANDS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by an exciting new Record Label started by two industry veterans with a very impressive track record!

Take a listen to the following references we got directly from them to get an idea of what might get this really cool Record Label interested:

"Underestimate Me" by Maggie Rose

"Love On" by Selena Gomez

"I Feel Like Dancing" by Jason Mraz

NOTE: This Label would love it if they heard some Songs recorded with live instrumentation, but "in the box" recordings could work too!

Please submit well-crafted Adult Contemporary/Pop Songs with radio-friendly, commercial appeal that showcases your unique sound and style! Catchy melodies, hooky choruses, infectious rhythms, excellent musicianship, and well-written lyrics are all needed for this request. Instrumentation that blends Adult Contemporary with Pop sensibilities, and is in the general stylistic ballpark of the reference Songs will work best. Please make sure that any virtual instruments or samples you use are high-quality and not dated-sounding. Great vocals that help sell your brand as an artist will be very helpful!

Your recording quality needs to be clean, clear, well-balanced, and good enough to represent your Songs well. Do NOT copy the references in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tone, texture, and overall vibe.

Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD, and please include lyrics, a photo, and a bio. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by a TAXI A&R Team Member who has a strong relationship with the Client. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Wednesday, May 15th, 2024. TAXI # S240515AC

opportunities.name: ORIGINAL BLUEGRASS INSTRUMENTALS
opportunities.request_description:
ORIGINAL BLUEGRASS INSTRUMENTALS are needed by a Film/TV Music Publisher for (up to) $5,000 placements in an upcoming Hulu Series!

This Publisher is on the hunt for Mid Tempo Instrumentals that could work as a replacement for "Another Night" by Ricky Skaggs:

"Another Night" by Ricky Skaggs

Although the reference has vocals, please submit Instrumentals only for this request.

IMPORTANT: They're NOT looking for clones or soundalikes! Similar tempo, style, and overall vibe? Yes. Clones? No!

QUOTING THE COMPANY: "We like the mid-tempo and acoustic approach of "Another Night" by Ricky Skaggs, and would like to hear instrumentals with the same mood, vibe, and energy."

Please send in original, well-crafted Bluegrass Instrumentals with lots of deep-south vibes and authentic Bluegrass musicianship! Your submissions should have depression-era motifs, expressive musical performances, sparse melodies, swung rhythms, and dynamic arrangements with plenty of forward motion and interest. Bluegrass instrumentation that's in the general stylistic wheelhouse of the reference will work best for this opportunity, such as acoustic guitar, banjo, fiddle, mandolin, etc. Live instrumentation is strongly suggested, but if you choose to use virtual instruments or samples, make sure they are high-quality, very realistic-sounding, and appropriate for the genre.

All submissions should be roughly 2 to 4 minutes in length (give or take). Non-faded, Buttoned endings will work best. Please do NOT copy the referenced material in any way, shape, or form. Use it only as a general guide for tempo, texture, tone, and overall vibe. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

NOTE: The sync fees we were quoted were up to $5,000; however, our experience tells us that number is probably based on them licensing Instrumentals from a well-known act through a big publisher like Sony or Universal. We think the sync fees could be lower (in the $1,500 to $2,500 range) for an unknown, independent act or music licensed from a music library. It could go higher – we’re just being cautious and conservative.

This Publisher offers a NON-EXCLUSIVE, 50/50 deal. You’ll split any applicable sync fees 50/50. You’ll keep 100% of the Master rights and the Writer’s share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's Share for any placements they generate. You must own or control your Masters and Copyright to submit for this opportunity. Please submit as many Instrumentals as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by a TAXI screener that was handpicked by the Music Publisher. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Thursday, May 9th, 2024. TAXI # S240509UE

opportunities.name: Lots of SONGS
opportunities.request_description:
Lots of SONGS about MONSTERS and BEASTS (in a wide range of genres and styles) with Male or Female vocals are needed by an A-List Sync and Music Licensing Company with a very successful track record of placements in Film, TV, and Commercials.

Due to the wide-ranging nature of this request, we didn't include references, as we felt they could potentially be more misleading or limiting than helpful.

QUOTING THE COMPANY: "We need Songs about monsters or beasts."

Please submit original Songs in a wide range of styles that fit the lyrical themes mentioned above! Submissions should have well-thought-out melodies, memorable choruses, dynamic rhythms, and solid arrangements. Since this listing is open to a wide range of styles and genres, instrumentation may vary based on which direction you choose to go, as long as it is consistent and competitive with other Songs in your chosen style. Please be sure your productions and any virtual sounds or samples you use are high-quality and not dated-sounding. Captivating, well-performed vocals are needed.

NOTE: They're looking for popular/commercially viable genres, including (but not limited to): Pop, Country, Rock, Singer-Songwriter, Folk, EDM, R&B/Soul, Rap/Hip-Hop, etc. We recommend that you avoid submitting anything in genres that don't have a lot of mainstream appeal!

Lyrics should be generally focused on the themes listed above and should avoid references to specific names, dates, times, places, brands, and profanity as well. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This company offers an EXCLUSIVE, 50/50 deal, so please be sure the Songs you pitch for this opportunity are NOT already signed with any other Companies or Catalogs. Any sync fees will be split 50/50 with the Company. You'll get 100% of the Writer's share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's share. You must own or control your Master and Copyright to submit. Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Monday, May 13th, 2024. TAXI # S240513ST

opportunities.name: Lots of GRITTY COUNTRY/WESTERN SONGS
opportunities.request_description:
Lots of GRITTY COUNTRY/WESTERN SONGS with MALE Vocals are needed by an A-List Sync and Music Licensing Company with a long list of notable placements in Film, TV, and Commercials.

This Company is searching for Songs in the general stylistic wheelhouse of the following references:

"Sleeping on the Blacktop" by Colter Wall

"Soul Of A Man" by David Lindley

"Everybody Walkin' This Land" by Paul Cauthen

QUOTING THE COMPANY: "We're looking for chunky, gritty western-style tracks with a male vocal (low & gritty is a bonus). Songs should be current and have been recorded in the last 5 years or so. Lyrical themes about heroes and villains, law, justice, blood, or other related topics are what we are looking for."

Please submit Country/Western Songs full of grit, and lyrics that match the themes listed above! Your submissions should have gravelly melodies, memorable choruses, engaging rhythms, and well-written lyrics. Instrumentation in the general wheelhouse of the references will work best for this opportunity, such as acoustic/slide guitar, banjo, harmonica, etc. We recommend using real instruments, but if you use any virtual instruments or samples, they should be high-quality, genre-appropriate, and realistic sounding. Authentic, and well-performed Male vocals are needed.

VERY IMPORTANT: This Company is NOT looking for modern Country Songs or anything with an overly-produced sound. Please pay extra close attention to the references to get a good take on their overall vibe, while taking extra care not to copy or clone them.

Lyrics should avoid references to specific names, dates, times, places, brands, and profanity. Please do NOT copy the referenced artists or songs in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a guide for tempo, texture, and tone. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This company offers an EXCLUSIVE, 50/50 deal, so please be sure the Songs you pitch for this opportunity are NOT already signed with any other Companies or Catalogs. Any sync fees will be split 50/50 with the Company. You'll get 100% of the Writer's share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's share. You must own or control your Master and Copyright to submit. Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Wednesday, May 22nd, 2024. TAXI # S240522WS

opportunities.name: COUNTRY ROCK ARTISTS
opportunities.request_description:
COUNTRY ROCK ARTISTS or BANDS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by a fairly new Record Label started by two industry veterans with a very impressive track record!

opportunities.request_description:

Please submit original Songs in a wide range of styles with a sentimental, inspirational, or uplifting sound and lyrics that fit the themes above! Submissions should have inspiring melodies, emotionally impactful choruses, dynamic rhythms, solid arrangements, and well-performed vocals. Since this listing is open to a wide range of styles and genres, instrumentation may vary based on which direction you choose to go, as long as it is consistent and competitive with other Songs in your chosen style. Please be sure any virtual sounds or samples you use are high-quality. Well-performed vocals that authentically convey the emotion behind your track and lyrics are needed.

NOTE: They're looking for popular/commercially viable genres, including (but not limited to): Pop, Country, Rock, Singer-Songwriter, Folk, EDM, R&B/Soul, Rap/Hip-Hop, etc. We recommend that you avoid submitting anything in genres that don't have a lot of mainstream appeal!

Lyrics should be centrally focused on the themes listed above, and should avoid references to specific names, dates, times, places, brands, and profanity as well. Please do NOT copy the referenced artist or song in any way, shape, or form. Use it only as a guide for tempo, texture, and tone. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This company offers an EXCLUSIVE, 50/50 deal, so please be sure the Songs you pitch for this opportunity are NOT already signed with any other Companies or Catalogs. Any sync fees will be split 50/50 with the Company. You'll get 100% of the Writer's share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's share. You must own or control your Master and Copyright to submit. Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Sunday, May 19th, 2024. TAXI # S240519UP

opportunities.name: ORIGINAL JAZZ INSTRUMENTALS
opportunities.request_description:
ORIGINAL JAZZ INSTRUMENTALS with SWING are needed by a Film/TV Music Publisher for (up to) $5,000 placements in an upcoming Hulu Series!

This Publisher is on the hunt for Mid Tempo Instrumentals that could be heard on a playlist with the following:

"The Way You Look Tonight" by Frank Sinatra

"Moonlight Becomes You" by Eddie Higgins

"I Can't Give You Anything but Love" by Billie Holiday

"April In Paris" by Count Basie

Although some of the references have vocals, please submit Instrumentals only for this request.

QUOTING THE COMPANY: "We are looking for old-school Jazz with swing. (some blues-influence could potentially work as well) They should have an emotionally upbeat/danceable sound, and they need to showcase personality, attitude, and character. They also need to evoke emotion and have a feel-good, positive vibe."

Please submit original, well-crafted Jazz Instrumentals with lots of positive vibes, danceable rhythms, and the type of sound that is reminiscent of "crooner-era" Jazz! Your submissions should have jazz-inspired motifs, expressive musical performances, feel-good melodies, swingin' rhythms, and dynamic arrangements with plenty of forward motion and interest. Jazz instrumentation that's in the general stylistic wheelhouse of the references will work best for this opportunity, such as brass, strings, piano, upright bass, drums, etc. Live instrumentation is strongly suggested, but if you choose to use virtual instruments or samples, make sure they are high-quality, very realistic-sounding, and appropriate for the genre.

NOTE: You can submit recently recorded Instrumentals in the general style of the reference, OR if you have high-quality vintage recordings (recorded back in the day), they would love to hear those as well!

All submissions should be roughly 2 to 4 minutes in length (give or take). Non-faded, Buttoned/Stinger endings will work best. Please do NOT copy the referenced material in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, texture, tone, and overall vibe. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

NOTE: The sync fees we were quoted were up to $5,000; however, our experience tells us that number is probably based on them licensing Instrumentals from a well-known act through a big publisher like Sony or Universal. We think the sync fees could be lower (in the $2,500 to $3,500 range) for an unknown, independent act or music licensed from a music library. It could go higher – we’re just being cautious and conservative.

This Publisher offers a NON-EXCLUSIVE, 50/50 deal. You’ll split any applicable sync fees 50/50. You’ll keep 100% of the Master rights and the Writer’s share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's Share for any placements they generate. You must own or control your Masters and Copyright to submit for this opportunity. Please submit as many Instrumentals as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by a TAXI screener that was handpicked by the Music Publisher. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Friday, May 10th, 2024. TAXI # S240510SG
