opportunities.name: MAINSTREAM ADULT CONTEMPORARY/POP ARTISTS
opportunities.request_description:
MAINSTREAM ADULT CONTEMPORARY/POP ARTISTS or BANDS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by an exciting new Record Label started by two industry veterans with a very impressive track record!

Take a listen to the following references we got directly from them to get an idea of what might get this really cool Record Label interested:

"A Given Thing" by Weyes Blood

"I Drink Wine" by Adele

"Chemtrails Over The Country Club" by Lana Del Rey

NOTE: This Label would love it if they heard some Songs recorded with live instrumentation, but "in-the-box" recordings could work too!

Please submit well-crafted Adult Contemporary/Pop Songs with radio-friendly, commercial appeal that showcases your unique sound and style! Catchy melodies, hooky choruses, engaging rhythms, excellent musicianship, and well-written lyrics are all needed for this request. Instrumentation that blends Adult Contemporary with Pop sensibilities and stays in the general stylistic ballpark of the reference Songs will work best. Please make sure that any virtual instruments or samples you use are high-quality and not dated-sounding. Great vocals that help sell your brand as an artist will be very helpful!

Your recording quality needs to be clean, clear, well-balanced, and good enough to represent your Songs well. Do NOT copy the references in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tone, texture, and overall vibe.

Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD, and please include lyrics, a photo, and a bio. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by a TAXI A&R Team Member who has a strong relationship with the Client. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Saturday, May 25th, 2024. TAXI # S240525DV

Your submissions should have unforgettable choruses, dynamic arrangements, great melodies, lots of mainstream appeal, solid musicianship, well-crafted lyrics, and a modern sound. (Nothing that sounds dated will work here!) Americana or Alt-Indie instrumentation that's in the general stylistic wheelhouse of the references will work best for this opportunity. opportunities.name: Lots of EMOTIONAL SONGS about
opportunities.request_description:
Lots of EMOTIONAL SONGS about LOSS (in a wide range of genres and styles) with Male or Female vocals are needed by an A-List Sync and Music Licensing Company with a very successful track record of placements in Film, TV, and Commercials.

Due to the wide-ranging nature of this request, we didn't include references, as we felt they could potentially be more misleading or limiting than helpful.

QUOTING THE COMPANY: "We need songs about loss, specifically related to survivors struggling to navigate grief and not always doing it with grace. Themes and lyrics need to hit on the multitude of emotions felt while trying to process and proceed. They also need to sound current and have been recorded within the last five years or so."

Please submit original Songs in a wide range of styles that deal with loss or grief, and the struggle of working through them. Submissions should be down-tempo and have somber melodies, meaningful choruses, solid arrangements, current-sounding productions, and well-performed vocals. Since this listing is open to a wide range of styles and genres, instrumentation may vary based on which direction you choose to go, as long as it is consistent and competitive with other Songs in your chosen style. Please be sure any virtual sounds or samples you use are high-quality. Modern and well-performed vocals that authentically convey the emotion behind your track and lyrics are needed.

NOTE: They're looking for popular/commercially viable genres that could work with the theme, including (but not limited to): Singer-Songwriter, Pop, Country, Folk, etc. We recommend that you avoid submitting anything in genres that don't naturally work with the theme or the down-tempo requirement.

Lyrics should be centrally focused on the theme listed above, and should avoid references to specific names, dates, times, places, brands, and profanity as well. Please do NOT copy the referenced artist or song in any way, shape, or form. Use it only as a guide for tempo, texture, and tone. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This company offers an EXCLUSIVE, 50/50 deal, so please be sure the Songs you pitch for this opportunity are NOT already signed with any other Companies or Catalogs. Any sync fees will be split 50/50 with the Company. You'll get 100% of the Writer's share, and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher's share. You must own or control your Master and Copyright to submit. Please submit as many Songs as you'd like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Wednesday, May 22nd, 2024. TAXI # S240522LS

Honest, authentic-sounding, and expressive vocal performances could go a long way in getting this publisher excited about signing and plugging your song!

Stripped-down demos and full productions are both okay to submit, as long as your Songs are great and your recordings are clean, clear, and well-balanced! Do NOT copy the references in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, texture, and overall vibe.

NOTEWORTHY: If time permits, someone from the Publisher's staff on Music Row (who has been trained as a TAXI screener) will screen the submissions for this request. That means that somebody who is directly involved in this request could be "ears-on" with your submissions.

opportunities.name: RELAXING  AMBIENT INSTRUMENTALS are
opportunities.request_description:
RELAXING  AMBIENT INSTRUMENTALS are needed by a brand new record Label/Publisher, started by highly experienced industry veterans with long, successful histories. This is an amazing opportunity to get in on the ground floor with an exciting new Company!

This Company is searching for a range of sparse, relaxing Instrumentals in the general stylistic ballpark of the following references:

"Flying: Relaxing Sleep Music" by Soothing Relaxation

"Deep Sleep Music" by Yellow Brick Cinema

"Fall Into Sleep Instantly" by Weightless

NOTE: Even though the references may have rain, fountain, and babbling brook sound effects, the Label does NOT want them. No SFX, please!

Quoting the Company: "This music is needed for yoga studios, spas, wellness centers, as well as worldwide digital releases on Spotify, Pandora, Apple Music, Youtube, etc. It needs to be VERY simple, and VERY sparse while creating a blissful, relaxing, sleep-inducing, dream-like state for the listener.

We're NOT looking for amazing compositional chops. This is MUCH more about creating a feeling of peace and serenity, as if the listener is wrapped in a warm blanket and letting go of everything around them. Moods can range from blissful, optimistic, introspective (but not so much as to be depressing), wondrous, tranquil, etc.

We’re looking for composers who can demonstrate that they understand that the music serves the specific purpose of lulling the listener(s) into a calm, relaxed state. Musical elements, melodies, and/or production styles that show off the composer’s chops will likely take the intended listeners out of their trance-like state, thus defeating the use and purpose of the music."

Please submit minimalist Instrumentals with a relaxing, sleep-inducing vibe and a peaceful, relaxing sound. Your submissions should have one central motif with minimal—to—no—melodic movement, and tranquil, soft sounds. Instrumentation should be ambient and relaxing, such as flowing synth pads, soft piano, muted keys, etc. Please avoid things like bell tree glissandos, triangles, bells, etc., or other elements that could be jarring to tranced-out listeners. Any samples or virtual instruments you use need to be high-quality.

Please ensure that your submissions remain very SIMPLE, but still maintain a level of artistry and originality. Imagine what you would hear while being hypnotized!

All submissions should be about 2 to 4 minutes long, give or take. Natural-sounding, faded endings and/or non-faded endings are both okay for this request. Do NOT copy the reference tracks in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, and overall vibe.

Please submit at least 2 tracks to show your range. If the company likes what they hear, they may contact you about doing a full album!

IMPORTANT: Your Submissions can NOT be commercially released on Spotify, Apple Music, etc., OR be encumbered by ANY other publishing, licensing, administration, and/or exploitation deals (whether non-exclusive or exclusive), including publishing/licensing agreements with CD Baby Pro, TuneCore, etc.

This company is a Label/Publisher hybrid, and offers an EXCLUSIVE 50/50 deal. Music signed to this deal will be signed exclusively to the company (under a nom de plume), but the composer/artist is non-exclusive and is free to release other material under their own name by themselves or for any other company – just not the same music or the same nom de plume. Please submit as many Instrumentals as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Saturday, May 25th, 2024. TAXI # S240525AM

opportunities.request_description:

This is a catalog you want to be in! Please listen to the following examples the Library's CEO gave us to get yourself in the ballpark of what they need:

Instrumental Examples

Quoting the Company's CEO: "The beginning should feel intimate and personal – like it's the beginning of a process. Then your arrangement should move forward with more instrumentation to create a sense of making progress. Finally, your pieces should have a positive, inspiring conclusion."

Please submit well-crafted Instrumental Cues full of inspirational and positive undertones! Even though the Library is asking for different sections, they only want Cues that stick to one melodic idea throughout! Pay extra close attention to how this is done in the references! Organic-based instrumentation that's in the general stylistic wheelhouse of the references will work best. Please be sure that any virtual instruments or samples you use are high-quality and realistic-sounding.

ADVICE DIRECTLY FROM THE LIBRARY'S CEO: "Many composers throw in way too many ideas and are not focused on ONE CENTRAL MOTIF: they try to keep things interesting by adding new harmonic lines and elements (melodies, even improvisations, etc) instead of focusing on the production and textures. All submissions should be about 2 minutes long, give or take. Non-faded, buttoned/stinger endings are required. Do NOT copy the references in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, texture, and overall vibe. Broadcast Quality is needed.

NOTE: This company has a strong preference for composers who understand music licensing companies and how typical music library deals are structured. If that's not you, they politely ask that you don't submit to this request.

This Music Library offers an EXCLUSIVE deal with a cool twist. You’ll keep 50% of all gross income generated by your music, plus you’ll get 100% of the Writer’s share income generated by your PRO. Because this is an Exclusive deal, the music you submit for this pitch cannot already be signed with other Libraries or Publishers. You must own or control 100% of your Master and Copyright. opportunities.name: REMOTE: For the Love of Bands (Blog)
opportunities.request_description: aaj
opportunities.request_opportunity_description: For the Love of Bands is a vibrant community that brings together music lovers, industry professionals, and talented artists. Our mission is simple: to provide a platform where deserving independent musicians can be heard and appreciated. We believe that great music knows no boundaries and can be found in every corner of the world.Whether you're an avid music fan searching for your new favorite artist, a musician looking for exposure and support, or an industry professional seeking fresh talent, For the Love of Bands has something for everyone. So, tune in, read our articles, explore our playlists, and immerse yourself in the world of independent music.
opportunities.request_band_description: We're looking to review independent and emerging artists and bandsNot open to HipHop, Rap, RnB, House, and TechnoActs must be actively playing shows and have upcoming shows and releasesOriginal music onlyActs must have a solid online presence

opportunities.description: For The Love Of Bands is a passionate music blog that understands how hard it is to get your newly recorded independent gems heard by the rest of the world. We believe in supporting independent and emerging artists and we post tips on navigating the music industry.For The Love Of Bands is looking for Sonicbids artists to feature! Apply today!

opportunities.name: Lots of COVERS of PUBLIC
opportunities.request_description:
Lots of COVERS of PUBLIC DOMAIN CHRISTMAS SONGS in ANY GENRE with Male or Female vocals are needed by a Brand New Music Licensing Company started by a seasoned industry pro! They already have distribution for their catalog, and this is a great opportunity to get in on the ground floor and build a new relationship with an awesome, new Music Library!

This Company is looking for Covers of Christmas Songs in the general ballpark of the following references:

"Silent Night" by Tyler Shaw

"Go Tell It on the Mountain" by Tori Kelly

"Angels We Have Heard On High" by Tinashe

"The First Noel" by Lady A

"What Child Is This" by Lauren Daigle

"Silent Night" by Michael Bublé

Please send them recently recorded Covers of Public Domain Christmas Songs (in any commercially viable genre) that are bursting with holiday spirit! Your submissions should have expressive and well-performed vocals, modern sounds and productions, and lots of commercial appeal. Since this listing is open to a wide range of sounds, styles, and genres, instrumentation may vary based on which direction you choose to go, as long as it is consistent and competitive with other Songs in your chosen style. Please stay true to the original melodies and lyrics! Your arrangements can lean more on the traditional to the very modern end of the holiday spectrum – just be sure your productions are current-sounding! Any virtual instruments or samples you use should be high-quality.

Quoting the CEO of the Company: "Your arrangement and orchestration should be unique. Do not copy other cover arrangements."

Please double-check to make sure the Covers you submit are truly Public Domain! In case you’re unsure if your Songs are in the Public Domain, here’s a link that will help: Public Domain Christmas Song List.

Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This Company offers an EXCLUSIVE deal, so the material you submit for this request CANNOT be signed with other publishers or catalogs. Sync fees will be split 50/50. You must own or control your Master to submit for this opportunity. Please submit as many Covers as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Sunday, June 2nd, 2024. TAXI # S240602MS

opportunities.name: Lots of ORIGINAL CHRISTMAS SONGS

QUOTING THE CEO: "Lyrics should be universal and contain references to Christmas or Christmas-related activities."

Please submit original, well-crafted Christmas Songs in your (commercially viable) genre of choice with lots of festive sounds and lyrical themes! Your submissions should have cheery melodies, engaging rhythms/beats, and lots of holiday spirit (please don't send anything that is melancholy or emotionally down.) Since the listing is open to a wide variety of genres, instrumentation may vary based on which direction you go, as long as your submissions are competitive with other Songs in your chosen style. Please be sure that any virtual instruments or samples you use are high quality and appropriate for the style of your Songs. Expressive and well-performed vocals are key!

NOTE: They're looking for popular/commercially viable genres, including (but not limited to): Pop, Country, Rock, Singer-Songwriter, Folk, EDM, R&B/Soul, Rap/Hip-Hop, etc. We recommend that you avoid submitting anything in genres that don't have a lot of mainstream appeal!

Lyrics should be Christmas-themed and should avoid profanity. Please do NOT copy the referenced artists or songs in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a guide for tempo, texture, and tone. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

This Company offers an EXCLUSIVE deal, so the material you submit for this request CANNOT be signed with other publishers or catalogs. Sync fees will be split 50/50. The Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher’s share, and you’ll keep 100% of the Writer’s share. You must own or control your Master and Copyright to submit for this opportunity. Please submit as many Songs as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Tuesday, June 4th, 2024. TAXI # S240604AG

opportunities.name: INDIE ELECTRO-POP SONGS
opportunities.request_description:
INDIE ELECTRO-POP SONGS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by a “TV/Film sync-oriented” Record Label started by a Multi-Platinum Producer and a team of very successful industry veterans!

This Label is searching for Mid-to-Up-Tempo Songs in the general wheelhouse of the following references:

"Line Of Sight" by ODESZA ft. WYNNE & Mansionair

"Wild Things" by LAUREL

"Foreign Obstacles" by Mvlholland

Please submit well-crafted Indie Electro-Pop Songs with tons of energy, modern productions, and lots of commercial appeal! Your submissions should have catchy melodies, great rhythms, ear-worm hooks, and well-written lyrics. Instrumentation that blends Pop and Electro music and is in the general stylistic ballpark of the reference tracks will work best. Please be sure that any virtual instruments or samples you use are high-quality and not dated-sounding. Confident, well-performed Male or Female vocals are needed!

Lyric Tip: While not specified, we think that clean lyrics will likely work best for this "TV/Film sync-oriented" opportunity. Avoiding references to specific brands, places, dates, times, and people, etc. is probably a good idea, as well.

Your recording quality needs to be clean, clear, and well-balanced so that it represents your Songs well. Do NOT copy the referenced examples in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide to get you in the stylistic ballpark of the overall texture and tone.

IMPORTANT NOTE: This company has specifically asked that you only send unreleased Songs that aren't already commercially available. If you've already released them on Spotify, Apple Music, etc., or if they’re already published or administered by CD Baby Pro, Tune Core, etc., please do not submit them.

REALLY IMPORTANT: This company is not just looking for a song or two from you. They’re looking to build professional, ongoing relationships with artists who are highly committed to working hard, and have the drive and ability to deliver a lot of super-strong material. Having the right type of image and “looking the part” could be icing on the cake, but first and foremost, it's about having great music and a strong work ethic!

The specific deal points will be handled on a case-by-case basis between you and the Label. You must own or control your Master and Copyright to submit to this opportunity. Please submit as many Songs as you’d like, online or per CD. Include lyrics, a photo, and a bio. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Sunday, June 2nd, 2024. TAXI # S240602CT

opportunities.name: Lots of FUNKY HIP-HOP SONGS
opportunities.request_description:
Lots of FUNKY HIP-HOP SONGS with Male or Female Vocals are needed by an extremely busy Music Library with a tremendously long list of killer placements in Hit TV Shows!

This Company is looking for Mid-to-Up-Tempo Songs in the general ballpark of these references:

"We Don't Stop" by Raphael Lake, Aaron Levy, & Wesley Smith

"Do What I Do" by William Davies

"Do It" by Spank 

Please submit Hip-Hop Songs with tons of energy, old-school Hip-Hop influences, and lots of funky vibes! Your submissions should have slick lyrical flows, memorable hooks, hard-hitting rhythms, funky motifs, and well-crafted lyrics. Instrumentation that falls in the general stylistic ballpark of the references and others like them will work best. Please make sure your productions and any virtual instruments or samples you use are high-quality and genre-appropriate. Confident, expressive, and well-performed vocals are key for this listing!

Lyrics that avoid references to specific names, dates, times, brands, and profanity are strongly recommended. Do NOT copy the reference tracks in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, and overall vibe. Do NOT submit any material with unauthorized samples of any other artists’ music, sounds, or any other form of media. Broadcast Quality is needed.

NOTE: Do NOT submit any tracks with spoken producer tags/watermarks, as they're not usable for film and TV placements.

IMPORTANT: Cleared sample libraries are okay to use, but any samples or loops you include in your pieces should be altered enough that they're distinguishable from the originals. Basically, if you Shazamed one of your tracks and another artist's song comes up, your music would definitely be disqualified by this Company.

ALSO IMPORTANT: Your Submissions can NOT be commercially released on Spotify, Apple Music, etc., OR be encumbered by ANY other publishing, licensing, administration, and/or exploitation deals (whether non-exclusive or exclusive), including publishing/licensing agreements with CD Baby Pro, TuneCore, etc.

This company offers an EXCLUSIVE deal. You’ll split all upfront sync fees 50/50. You’ll keep 100% of the Writer’s share and the Publisher will get 100% of the Publisher’s share. You must own or control your Master and Copyright. Since this is an EXCLUSIVE deal, please be sure the material you submit for this pitch is not already signed with other Libraries or Catalogs. Please submit as many Songs as you’d like, online or per CD. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Saturday, June 2nd, 2024. TAXI # S240602FH

opportunities.name: A Wide
opportunities.request_description:
A Wide Range of MODERN INSTRUMENTAL JAZZ ARTISTS or BANDS are needed by a U.K.-based Record Label. They're on the prowl for some exciting acts to sign, and we'd love for you to be one of them!!

NOTEWORTHY: This Label signed a TAXI Member, and they found them through a listing just like this!!!

Take a listen to the references below to get an idea of what might get this amazing Record Label interested:

"Street Fighter Mas" by Kamasi Washington

"Keep On" by Alfa Mist

"24th & Lake" by Terrace Martin & Curly

Please send in well-crafted Jazz Instrumentals that showcase your one-of-a-kind sound and musical abilities! Your submissions should have excellent musicianship and genre-appropriate arrangements with plenty of forward motion and interest. A cutting-edge, modern sound and style is what this Label is looking for! Jazz instrumentation that's in the general stylistic ballpark of the references will work best. Live instrumentation is strongly recommended, but if you choose to use virtual instruments or samples, please make sure they are high-quality and not dated-sounding.

TAXI Tip: We know that Jazz is a pretty wide-ranging genre. This Company is definitely looking for cool, unique Artists to sign, but your submissions shouldn't be so "out there" and/or "abstract" that they have zero commercial appeal.

NOTE: This Label is interested in artists and bands that are actively building their careers. In your bio, please include any touring, fan base, sales, streaming, and social media figures you may have. If you’re an artist or band that’s just starting out and you don’t have much of a story or track record yet, but you DO have an amazing sound and some killer Instrumentals to back it up, they still want to hear you!

We recommend that you submit at least THREE TRACKS per submission so they can see if you’ve got depth in your material.

Your productions and recording quality need to be clean, clear, well-balanced, and good enough to represent your Tracks well. Do NOT copy the references in any way, shape, or form. Use them only as a general guide for tempo, tone, texture, and overall vibe.

Please submit as many Instrumentals as you'd like, online or per CD, and please include a photo and a bio. All submissions will be screened and critiqued by TAXI. Submissions must be received no later than 11:59 PM (PDT) on Monday, June 3rd, 2024. TAXI # S240603ZZ

opportunities.name: CONTEMPORARY SINGER/SONGWRITER SONGS
opportunities.request_description:
CONTEMPORARY SINGER/SONGWRITER SONGS in a FOREIGN LANGUAGE with Male or Female Vocals are needed by a U.K.-based Music & Media Company that's constantly landing placements in TV Shows, Film, and other Media.

We purposely avoided putting references in this request as we felt they could be more misleading or limiting than helpful.

Songs can be in languages as wide-ranging as Korean, Swahili, Arabic, Amharic, French, Italian, Spanish, Mandarin, Russian, Hindi, Japanese, etc. Just no English, please! Naturally, more common languages will be more appealing to the client. Obscure languages from lesser-known countries could be less appealing to the Company because there will likely be less demand for those.

Please submit well-crafted Singer/Songwriter Songs with captivating melodies, well-performed vocals, and plenty of mainstream appeal. Your submissions should have engaging, well-crafted lyrics, memorable choruses, and lots of genuine, emotional energy that could work well for placements in TV and Film.
